---
<BaseLayout title="Codebolt SDK — Embed the Engine in Your Product" navbarVariant="solid" site={site} navigation={navigation}>
  <PageHeader
    title="Codebolt SDK"
    subtitle="Embed the engine in your own product. Build a custom client, ship an agent-native app, or run the engine inside your infrastructure."
  />
  <CenteredText
    variant="thesis"
    text="The Editor is one client of the engine. The CLI is another. With the SDK, you can build your own — a vertical IDE for your domain, an agent-powered SaaS for your customers, or a headless deployment running inside your CI. Same engine. Your interface."
  />
  <FeatureBlock
    heading="Three SDKs, three layers of access"
    body="Agent SDK (codeboltjs, 63+ modules): write the agent loop in code. Plugin SDK (3 channels: WebSocket, Mux, HTTP): extend the engine itself. Client SDK (72 REST + 33 WS): build any front-end you want. The engine is open at every layer — you choose where to plug in."
    diagram="Agent SDK    → write custom agents
Plugin SDK   → extend the engine
Client SDK   → build your own UI

63+ modules · 3 channels
72 REST + 33 WS endpoints
All open. All documented.
"
  />
  <FeatureBlock
    heading="Ship agent-native software"
    body="If your product needs agents at the core — not as a chat sidebar — the SDK is the foundation. The engine handles the agentic loop, memory, plugins, and coordination. You build the surface your customers see. Cursor and Claude Code can't be embedded; the Codebolt engine can."
    reverse={true}
    diagram="Your product:
├── Your UI / brand
├── Your auth / billing
├── Your domain logic
└── Codebolt Engine ← embedded
    ├── Agents
    ├── Plugins
    └── Memory

You own the product.
The engine does the work.
"
  />
  <FeatureBlock
    heading="Self-host the engine"
    body="Run the engine on your own infrastructure — bare metal, Docker, Kubernetes, your VPC. The Client SDK connects any front-end to a self-hosted engine instance the same way it connects to Cloud. Compliance teams get a deployment model they can audit."
    diagram="$ docker run codebolt/engine:latest
$ codebolt serve --port 3100

# Engine running on your infra
# Connect any client (Editor, CLI,
# custom UI) to the same engine
# Self-host = full control
"
  />
  <ComparisonColumns
    problem={{"heading":"Closed agent products","items":["Cursor, Claude Code, Devin — you can use them, you can't embed them","No way to ship an agent-native product on their engine","No self-host story for compliance-heavy environments","Front-end is fixed; you can't build a vertical UX","Lock-in to one vendor's surface"]}}
    solution={{"heading":"Codebolt SDK","items":["Engine is embeddable — build a product on top of it","Three SDKs let you plug in at agent, plugin, or client layer","Self-host on your infra, your VPC, your terms","Build any front-end — vertical IDE, SaaS, internal tool","The engine is yours to deploy as you see fit"]}}
  />
  <CtaBlock
